Carl Gilliard https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Gilliard 0 Carl Rousseau Gilliard (born April 18, 1958) is an American actor, director, and producer. Gilliard started his career working as a radio newscaster at WGPR in Detroit. He moved to Los Angeles in 1985, where he appeared in over 2 dozen plays. He has also appeared in films such as Inception, The Lost Shepherd, and Retiring Tatiana. Gilliard currently resides in Palmdale, California.
